{"questionId":"22937","questionHtml":"<p>Find the least value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> for which the edge <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>AF</mtext></math> will definitely not be used by Daniel.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>cycle starts: <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>ABCDEGHF</mtext></math></p>\n<p>return to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math> has two options, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>FA</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>18</mn></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>hence least value of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>19</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22937","referenceCode":"21N.3.AHL.TZ0.1e.i","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the least value of x for which the edge AF will definitely not be used by Daniel.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"e.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.14—Graph theory","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.15—Adjacency matrices and tables"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}